HEADWORD: Tufthunting
<hw>Tuft"hunt`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The practice of seeking
after, and hanging on, noblemen, or persons of quality, especially in
English universities.</def> <mark>[Cant, Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

